3091/*
3092 * ata_scsi_map_proto - Map pass-thru protocol value to taskfile value.
3093 * @byte1: Byte 1 from pass-thru CDB.
3094 *
3095 * RETURNS:
3096 * ATA_PROT_UNKNOWN if mapping failed/unimplemented, protocol otherwise.
3097 */
3098static u8
3099ata_scsi_map_proto(u8 byte1)
3100{
3101 switch((byte1 & 0x1e) >> 1) {
3102 case 3: /* Non-data */
3103 return ATA_PROT_NODATA;
3104
3105 case 6: /* DMA */
3106 case 10: /* UDMA Data-in */
3107 case 11: /* UDMA Data-Out */
3108 return ATA_PROT_DMA;
3109
3110 case 4: /* PIO Data-in */
3111 case 5: /* PIO Data-out */
3112 return ATA_PROT_PIO;
3113
3114 case 12: /* FPDMA */
3115 return ATA_PROT_NCQ;
3116
3117 case 0: /* Hard Reset */
3118 case 1: /* SRST */
3119 case 8: /* Device Diagnostic */
3120 case 9: /* Device Reset */
3121 case 7: /* DMA Queued */
3122 case 15: /* Return Response Info */
3123 default: /* Reserved */
3124 break;
3125 }
3126
3127 return ATA_PROT_UNKNOWN;
3128}
3129
3130/**
3131 * ata_scsi_pass_thru - convert ATA pass-thru CDB to taskfile
3132 * @qc: command structure to be initialized
3133 *
3134 * Handles either 12, 16, or 32-byte versions of the CDB.
3135 *
3136 * RETURNS:
3137 * Zero on success, non-zero on failure.
3138 */
3139static unsigned int ata_scsi_pass_thru(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
3140{
3141 struct ata_taskfile *tf = &(qc->tf);
3142 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
3143 struct ata_device *dev = qc->dev;
3144 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
3145 u16 fp;
3146 u16 cdb_offset = 0;
3147
3148 /* 7Fh variable length cmd means a ata pass-thru(32) */
3149 if (cdb[0] == VARIABLE_LENGTH_CMD)
3150 cdb_offset = 9;
3151
3152 tf->protocol = ata_scsi_map_proto(cdb[1 + cdb_offset]);
3153 if (tf->protocol == ATA_PROT_UNKNOWN) {
3154 fp = 1;
3155 goto invalid_fld;
3156 }
3157
3158 if (ata_is_ncq(tf->protocol) && (cdb[2 + cdb_offset] & 0x3) == 0)
3159 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NCQ_NODATA;
3160
3161 /* enable LBA */
3162 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_LBA;
3163
3164 /*
3165 * 12 and 16 byte CDBs use different offsets to
3166 * provide the various register values.
3167 */
3168 if (cdb[0] == ATA_16) {
3169 /*
3170 * 16-byte CDB - may contain extended commands.
3171 *
3172 * If that is the case, copy the upper byte register values.
3173 */
3174 if (cdb[1] & 0x01) {
3175 tf->hob_feature = cdb[3];
3176 tf->hob_nsect = cdb[5];
3177 tf->hob_lbal = cdb[7];
3178 tf->hob_lbam = cdb[9];
3179 tf->hob_lbah = cdb[11];
3180 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3181 } else
3182 tf->flags &= ~ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3183
3184 /*
3185 * Always copy low byte, device and command registers.
3186 */
3187 tf->feature = cdb[4];
3188 tf->nsect = cdb[6];
3189 tf->lbal = cdb[8];
3190 tf->lbam = cdb[10];
3191 tf->lbah = cdb[12];
3192 tf->device = cdb[13];
3193 tf->command = cdb[14];
3194 } else if (cdb[0] == ATA_12) {
3195 /*
3196 * 12-byte CDB - incapable of extended commands.
3197 */
3198 tf->flags &= ~ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3199
3200 tf->feature = cdb[3];
3201 tf->nsect = cdb[4];
3202 tf->lbal = cdb[5];
3203 tf->lbam = cdb[6];
3204 tf->lbah = cdb[7];
3205 tf->device = cdb[8];
3206 tf->command = cdb[9];
3207 } else {
3208 /*
3209 * 32-byte CDB - may contain extended command fields.
3210 *
3211 * If that is the case, copy the upper byte register values.
3212 */
3213 if (cdb[10] & 0x01) {
3214 tf->hob_feature = cdb[20];
3215 tf->hob_nsect = cdb[22];
3216 tf->hob_lbal = cdb[16];
3217 tf->hob_lbam = cdb[15];
3218 tf->hob_lbah = cdb[14];
3219 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3220 } else
3221 tf->flags &= ~ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3222
3223 tf->feature = cdb[21];
3224 tf->nsect = cdb[23];
3225 tf->lbal = cdb[19];
3226 tf->lbam = cdb[18];
3227 tf->lbah = cdb[17];
3228 tf->device = cdb[24];
3229 tf->command = cdb[25];
3230 tf->auxiliary = get_unaligned_be32(&cdb[28]);
3231 }
3232
3233 /* For NCQ commands copy the tag value */
3234 if (ata_is_ncq(tf->protocol))
3235 tf->nsect = qc->tag << 3;
3236
3237 /* enforce correct master/slave bit */
3238 tf->device = dev->devno ?
3239 tf->device | ATA_DEV1 : tf->device & ~ATA_DEV1;
3240
3241 switch (tf->command) {
3242 /* READ/WRITE LONG use a non-standard sect_size */
3243 case ATA_CMD_READ_LONG:
3244 case ATA_CMD_READ_LONG_ONCE:
3245 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_LONG:
3246 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_LONG_ONCE:
3247 if (tf->protocol != ATA_PROT_PIO || tf->nsect != 1) {
3248 fp = 1;
3249 goto invalid_fld;
3250 }
3251 qc->sect_size = scsi_bufflen(scmd);
3252 break;
3253
3254 /* commands using reported Logical Block size (e.g. 512 or 4K) */
3255 case ATA_CMD_CFA_WRITE_NE:
3256 case ATA_CMD_CFA_TRANS_SECT:
3257 case ATA_CMD_CFA_WRITE_MULT_NE:
3258 /* XXX: case ATA_CMD_CFA_WRITE_SECTORS_WITHOUT_ERASE: */
3259 case ATA_CMD_READ:
3260 case ATA_CMD_READ_EXT:
3261 case ATA_CMD_READ_QUEUED:
3262 /* XXX: case ATA_CMD_READ_QUEUED_EXT: */
3263 case ATA_CMD_FPDMA_READ:
3264 case ATA_CMD_READ_MULTI:
3265 case ATA_CMD_READ_MULTI_EXT:
3266 case ATA_CMD_PIO_READ:
3267 case ATA_CMD_PIO_READ_EXT:
3268 case ATA_CMD_READ_STREAM_DMA_EXT:
3269 case ATA_CMD_READ_STREAM_EXT:
3270 case ATA_CMD_VERIFY:
3271 case ATA_CMD_VERIFY_EXT:
3272 case ATA_CMD_WRITE:
3273 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_EXT:
3274 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_FUA_EXT:
3275 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_QUEUED:
3276 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_QUEUED_FUA_EXT:
3277 case ATA_CMD_FPDMA_WRITE:
3278 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_MULTI:
3279 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_MULTI_EXT:
3280 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_MULTI_FUA_EXT:
3281 case ATA_CMD_PIO_WRITE:
3282 case ATA_CMD_PIO_WRITE_EXT:
3283 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_STREAM_DMA_EXT:
3284 case ATA_CMD_WRITE_STREAM_EXT:
3285 qc->sect_size = scmd->device->sector_size;
3286 break;
3287
3288 /* Everything else uses 512 byte "sectors" */
3289 default:
3290 qc->sect_size = ATA_SECT_SIZE;
3291 }
3292
3293 /*
3294 * Set flags so that all registers will be written, pass on
3295 * write indication (used for PIO/DMA setup), result TF is
3296 * copied back and we don't whine too much about its failure.
3297 */
3298 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_ISADDR | ATA_TFLAG_DEVICE;
3299 if (scmd->sc_data_direction == DMA_TO_DEVICE)
3300 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_WRITE;
3301
3302 qc->flags |= ATA_QCFLAG_RESULT_TF | ATA_QCFLAG_QUIET;
3303
3304 /*
3305 * Set transfer length.
3306 *
3307 * TODO: find out if we need to do more here to
3308 * cover scatter/gather case.
3309 */
3310 ata_qc_set_pc_nbytes(qc);
3311
3312 /* We may not issue DMA commands if no DMA mode is set */
3313 if (tf->protocol == ATA_PROT_DMA && dev->dma_mode == 0) {
3314 fp = 1;
3315 goto invalid_fld;
3316 }
3317
3318 /* We may not issue NCQ commands to devices not supporting NCQ */
3319 if (ata_is_ncq(tf->protocol) && !ata_ncq_enabled(dev)) {
3320 fp = 1;
3321 goto invalid_fld;
3322 }
3323
3324 /* sanity check for pio multi commands */
3325 if ((cdb[1] & 0xe0) && !is_multi_taskfile(tf)) {
3326 fp = 1;
3327 goto invalid_fld;
3328 }
3329
3330 if (is_multi_taskfile(tf)) {
3331 unsigned int multi_count = 1 << (cdb[1] >> 5);
3332
3333 /* compare the passed through multi_count
3334 * with the cached multi_count of libata
3335 */
3336 if (multi_count != dev->multi_count)
3337 ata_dev_warn(dev, "invalid multi_count %u ignored\n",
3338 multi_count);
3339 }
3340
3341 /*
3342 * Filter SET_FEATURES - XFER MODE command -- otherwise,
3343 * SET_FEATURES - XFER MODE must be preceded/succeeded
3344 * by an update to hardware-specific registers for each
3345 * controller (i.e. the reason for ->set_piomode(),
3346 * ->set_dmamode(), and ->post_set_mode() hooks).
3347 */
3348 if (tf->command == ATA_CMD_SET_FEATURES &&
3349 tf->feature == SETFEATURES_XFER) {
3350 fp = (cdb[0] == ATA_16) ? 4 : 3;
3351 goto invalid_fld;
3352 }
3353
3354 /*
3355 * Filter TPM commands by default. These provide an
3356 * essentially uncontrolled encrypted "back door" between
3357 * applications and the disk. Set libata.allow_tpm=1 if you
3358 * have a real reason for wanting to use them. This ensures
3359 * that installed software cannot easily mess stuff up without
3360 * user intent. DVR type users will probably ship with this enabled
3361 * for movie content management.
3362 *
3363 * Note that for ATA8 we can issue a DCS change and DCS freeze lock
3364 * for this and should do in future but that it is not sufficient as
3365 * DCS is an optional feature set. Thus we also do the software filter
3366 * so that we comply with the TC consortium stated goal that the user
3367 * can turn off TC features of their system.
3368 */
3369 if (tf->command >= 0x5C && tf->command <= 0x5F && !libata_allow_tpm) {
3370 fp = (cdb[0] == ATA_16) ? 14 : 9;
3371 goto invalid_fld;
3372 }
3373
3374 return 0;
3375
3376 invalid_fld:
3377 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, scmd, fp, 0xff);
3378 return 1;
3379}
3380
3381/**
3382 * ata_format_dsm_trim_descr() - SATL Write Same to DSM Trim
3383 * @cmd: SCSI command being translated
3384 * @trmax: Maximum number of entries that will fit in sector_size bytes.
3385 * @sector: Starting sector
3386 * @count: Total Range of request in logical sectors
3387 *
3388 * Rewrite the WRITE SAME descriptor to be a DSM TRIM little-endian formatted
3389 * descriptor.
3390 *
3391 * Upto 64 entries of the format:
3392 * 63:48 Range Length
3393 * 47:0 LBA
3394 *
3395 * Range Length of 0 is ignored.
3396 * LBA's should be sorted order and not overlap.
3397 *
3398 * NOTE: this is the same format as ADD LBA(S) TO NV CACHE PINNED SET
3399 *
3400 * Return: Number of bytes copied into sglist.
3401 */
3402static size_t ata_format_dsm_trim_descr(struct scsi_cmnd *cmd, u32 trmax,
3403 u64 sector, u32 count)
3404{
3405 struct scsi_device *sdp = cmd->device;
3406 size_t len = sdp->sector_size;
3407 size_t r;
3408 __le64 *buf;
3409 u32 i = 0;
3410 unsigned long flags;
3411
3412 WARN_ON(len > ATA_SCSI_RBUF_SIZE);
3413
3414 if (len > ATA_SCSI_RBUF_SIZE)
3415 len = ATA_SCSI_RBUF_SIZE;
3416
3417 spin_lock_irqsave(&ata_scsi_rbuf_lock, flags);
3418 buf = ((void *)ata_scsi_rbuf);
3419 memset(buf, 0, len);
3420 while (i < trmax) {
3421 u64 entry = sector |
3422 ((u64)(count > 0xffff ? 0xffff : count) << 48);
3423 buf[i++] = __cpu_to_le64(entry);
3424 if (count <= 0xffff)
3425 break;
3426 count -= 0xffff;
3427 sector += 0xffff;
3428 }
3429 r = sg_copy_from_buffer(scsi_sglist(cmd), scsi_sg_count(cmd), buf, len);
3430 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ata_scsi_rbuf_lock, flags);
3431
3432 return r;
3433}
3434
3435/**
3436 * ata_scsi_write_same_xlat() - SATL Write Same to ATA SCT Write Same
3437 * @qc: Command to be translated
3438 *
3439 * Translate a SCSI WRITE SAME command to be either a DSM TRIM command or
3440 * an SCT Write Same command.
3441 * Based on WRITE SAME has the UNMAP flag:
3442 *
3443 * - When set translate to DSM TRIM
3444 * - When clear translate to SCT Write Same
3445 */
3446static unsigned int ata_scsi_write_same_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
3447{
3448 struct ata_taskfile *tf = &qc->tf;
3449 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
3450 struct scsi_device *sdp = scmd->device;
3451 size_t len = sdp->sector_size;
3452 struct ata_device *dev = qc->dev;
3453 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
3454 u64 block;
3455 u32 n_block;
3456 const u32 trmax = len >> 3;
3457 u32 size;
3458 u16 fp;
3459 u8 bp = 0xff;
3460 u8 unmap = cdb[1] & 0x8;
3461
3462 /* we may not issue DMA commands if no DMA mode is set */
3463 if (unlikely(!dev->dma_mode))
3464 goto invalid_opcode;
3465
3466 /*
3467 * We only allow sending this command through the block layer,
3468 * as it modifies the DATA OUT buffer, which would corrupt user
3469 * memory for SG_IO commands.
3470 */
3471 if (unlikely(blk_rq_is_passthrough(scmd->request)))
3472 goto invalid_opcode;
3473
3474 if (unlikely(scmd->cmd_len < 16)) {
3475 fp = 15;
3476 goto invalid_fld;
3477 }
3478 scsi_16_lba_len(cdb, &block, &n_block);
3479
3480 if (!unmap ||
3481 (dev->horkage & ATA_HORKAGE_NOTRIM) ||
3482 !ata_id_has_trim(dev->id)) {
3483 fp = 1;
3484 bp = 3;
3485 goto invalid_fld;
3486 }
3487 /* If the request is too large the cmd is invalid */
3488 if (n_block > 0xffff * trmax) {
3489 fp = 2;
3490 goto invalid_fld;
3491 }
3492
3493 /*
3494 * WRITE SAME always has a sector sized buffer as payload, this
3495 * should never be a multiple entry S/G list.
3496 */
3497 if (!scsi_sg_count(scmd))
3498 goto invalid_param_len;
3499
3500 /*
3501 * size must match sector size in bytes
3502 * For DATA SET MANAGEMENT TRIM in ACS-2 nsect (aka count)
3503 * is defined as number of 512 byte blocks to be transferred.
3504 */
3505
3506 size = ata_format_dsm_trim_descr(scmd, trmax, block, n_block);
3507 if (size != len)
3508 goto invalid_param_len;
3509
3510 if (ata_ncq_enabled(dev) && ata_fpdma_dsm_supported(dev)) {
3511 /* Newer devices support queued TRIM commands */
3512 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NCQ;
3513 tf->command = ATA_CMD_FPDMA_SEND;
3514 tf->hob_nsect = ATA_SUBCMD_FPDMA_SEND_DSM & 0x1f;
3515 tf->nsect = qc->tag << 3;
3516 tf->hob_feature = (size / 512) >> 8;
3517 tf->feature = size / 512;
3518
3519 tf->auxiliary = 1;
3520 } else {
3521 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_DMA;
3522 tf->hob_feature = 0;
3523 tf->feature = ATA_DSM_TRIM;
3524 tf->hob_nsect = (size / 512) >> 8;
3525 tf->nsect = size / 512;
3526 tf->command = ATA_CMD_DSM;
3527 }
3528
3529 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_ISADDR | ATA_TFLAG_DEVICE | ATA_TFLAG_LBA48 |
3530 ATA_TFLAG_WRITE;
3531
3532 ata_qc_set_pc_nbytes(qc);
3533
3534 return 0;
3535
3536invalid_fld:
3537 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, scmd, fp, bp);
3538 return 1;
3539invalid_param_len:
3540 /* "Parameter list length error" */
3541 ata_scsi_set_sense(dev, scmd, ILLEGAL_REQUEST, 0x1a, 0x0);
3542 return 1;
3543invalid_opcode:
3544 /* "Invalid command operation code" */
3545 ata_scsi_set_sense(dev, scmd, ILLEGAL_REQUEST, 0x20, 0x0);
3546 return 1;
3547}

3549/**
3550 * ata_scsiop_maint_in - Simulate a subset of MAINTENANCE_IN
3551 * @args: device MAINTENANCE_IN data / SCSI command of interest.
3552 * @rbuf: Response buffer, to which simulated SCSI cmd output is sent.
3553 *
3554 * Yields a subset to satisfy scsi_report_opcode()
3555 *
3556 * LOCKING:
3557 * spin_lock_irqsave(host lock)
3558 */
3559static unsigned int ata_scsiop_maint_in(struct ata_scsi_args *args, u8 *rbuf)
3560{
3561 struct ata_device *dev = args->dev;
3562 u8 *cdb = args->cmd->cmnd;
3563 u8 supported = 0;
3564 unsigned int err = 0;
3565
3566 if (cdb[2] != 1) {
3567 ata_dev_warn(dev, "invalid command format %d\n", cdb[2]);
3568 err = 2;
3569 goto out;
3570 }
3571 switch (cdb[3]) {
3572 case INQUIRY:
3573 case MODE_SENSE:
3574 case MODE_SENSE_10:
3575 case READ_CAPACITY:
3576 case SERVICE_ACTION_IN_16:
3577 case REPORT_LUNS:
3578 case REQUEST_SENSE:
3579 case SYNCHRONIZE_CACHE:
3580 case REZERO_UNIT:
3581 case SEEK_6:
3582 case SEEK_10:
3583 case TEST_UNIT_READY:
3584 case SEND_DIAGNOSTIC:
3585 case MAINTENANCE_IN:
3586 case READ_6:
3587 case READ_10:
3588 case READ_16:
3589 case WRITE_6:
3590 case WRITE_10:
3591 case WRITE_16:
3592 case ATA_12:
3593 case ATA_16:
3594 case VERIFY:
3595 case VERIFY_16:
3596 case MODE_SELECT:
3597 case MODE_SELECT_10:
3598 case START_STOP:
3599 supported = 3;
3600 break;
3601 case ZBC_IN:
3602 case ZBC_OUT:
3603 if (ata_id_zoned_cap(dev->id) ||
3604 dev->class == ATA_DEV_ZAC)
3605 supported = 3;
3606 break;
3607 case SECURITY_PROTOCOL_IN:
3608 case SECURITY_PROTOCOL_OUT:
3609 if (dev->flags & ATA_DFLAG_TRUSTED)
3610 supported = 3;
3611 break;
3612 default:
3613 break;
3614 }
3615out:
3616 rbuf[1] = supported; /* supported */
3617 return err;
3618}

3620/**
3621 * ata_scsi_report_zones_complete - convert ATA output
3622 * @qc: command structure returning the data
3623 *
3624 * Convert T-13 little-endian field representation into
3625 * T-10 big-endian field representation.
3626 * What a mess.
3627 */
3628static void ata_scsi_report_zones_complete(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
3629{
3630 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
3631 struct sg_mapping_iter miter;
3632 unsigned long flags;
3633 unsigned int bytes = 0;
3634
3635 sg_miter_start(&miter, scsi_sglist(scmd), scsi_sg_count(scmd),
3636 SG_MITER_TO_SG | SG_MITER_ATOMIC);
3637
3638 local_irq_save(flags);
3639 while (sg_miter_next(&miter)) {
3640 unsigned int offset = 0;
3641
3642 if (bytes == 0) {
3643 char *hdr;
3644 u32 list_length;
3645 u64 max_lba, opt_lba;
3646 u16 same;
3647
3648 /* Swizzle header */
3649 hdr = miter.addr;
3650 list_length = get_unaligned_le32(&hdr[0]);
3651 same = get_unaligned_le16(&hdr[4]);
3652 max_lba = get_unaligned_le64(&hdr[8]);
3653 opt_lba = get_unaligned_le64(&hdr[16]);
3654 put_unaligned_be32(list_length, &hdr[0]);
3655 hdr[4] = same & 0xf;
3656 put_unaligned_be64(max_lba, &hdr[8]);
3657 put_unaligned_be64(opt_lba, &hdr[16]);
3658 offset += 64;
3659 bytes += 64;
3660 }
3661 while (offset < miter.length) {
3662 char *rec;
3663 u8 cond, type, non_seq, reset;
3664 u64 size, start, wp;
3665
3666 /* Swizzle zone descriptor */
3667 rec = miter.addr + offset;
3668 type = rec[0] & 0xf;
3669 cond = (rec[1] >> 4) & 0xf;
3670 non_seq = (rec[1] & 2);
3671 reset = (rec[1] & 1);
3672 size = get_unaligned_le64(&rec[8]);
3673 start = get_unaligned_le64(&rec[16]);
3674 wp = get_unaligned_le64(&rec[24]);
3675 rec[0] = type;
3676 rec[1] = (cond << 4) | non_seq | reset;
3677 put_unaligned_be64(size, &rec[8]);
3678 put_unaligned_be64(start, &rec[16]);
3679 put_unaligned_be64(wp, &rec[24]);
3680 WARN_ON(offset + 64 > miter.length);
3681 offset += 64;
3682 bytes += 64;
3683 }
3684 }
3685 sg_miter_stop(&miter);
3686 local_irq_restore(flags);
3687
3688 ata_scsi_qc_complete(qc);
3689}
3690
3691static unsigned int ata_scsi_zbc_in_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
3692{
3693 struct ata_taskfile *tf = &qc->tf;
3694 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
3695 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
3696 u16 sect, fp = (u16)-1;
3697 u8 sa, options, bp = 0xff;
3698 u64 block;
3699 u32 n_block;
3700
3701 if (unlikely(scmd->cmd_len < 16)) {
3702 ata_dev_warn(qc->dev, "invalid cdb length %d\n",
3703 scmd->cmd_len);
3704 fp = 15;
3705 goto invalid_fld;
3706 }
3707 scsi_16_lba_len(cdb, &block, &n_block);
3708 if (n_block != scsi_bufflen(scmd)) {
3709 ata_dev_warn(qc->dev, "non-matching transfer count (%d/%d)\n",
3710 n_block, scsi_bufflen(scmd));
3711 goto invalid_param_len;
3712 }
3713 sa = cdb[1] & 0x1f;
3714 if (sa != ZI_REPORT_ZONES) {
3715 ata_dev_warn(qc->dev, "invalid service action %d\n", sa);
3716 fp = 1;
3717 goto invalid_fld;
3718 }
3719 /*
3720 * ZAC allows only for transfers in 512 byte blocks,
3721 * and uses a 16 bit value for the transfer count.
3722 */
3723 if ((n_block / 512) > 0xffff || n_block < 512 || (n_block % 512)) {
3724 ata_dev_warn(qc->dev, "invalid transfer count %d\n", n_block);
3725 goto invalid_param_len;
3726 }
3727 sect = n_block / 512;
3728 options = cdb[14] & 0xbf;
3729
3730 if (ata_ncq_enabled(qc->dev) &&
3731 ata_fpdma_zac_mgmt_in_supported(qc->dev)) {
3732 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NCQ;
3733 tf->command = ATA_CMD_FPDMA_RECV;
3734 tf->hob_nsect = ATA_SUBCMD_FPDMA_RECV_ZAC_MGMT_IN & 0x1f;
3735 tf->nsect = qc->tag << 3;
3736 tf->feature = sect & 0xff;
3737 tf->hob_feature = (sect >> 8) & 0xff;
3738 tf->auxiliary = ATA_SUBCMD_ZAC_MGMT_IN_REPORT_ZONES | (options << 8);
3739 } else {
3740 tf->command = ATA_CMD_ZAC_MGMT_IN;
3741 tf->feature = ATA_SUBCMD_ZAC_MGMT_IN_REPORT_ZONES;
3742 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_DMA;
3743 tf->hob_feature = options;
3744 tf->hob_nsect = (sect >> 8) & 0xff;
3745 tf->nsect = sect & 0xff;
3746 }
3747 tf->device = ATA_LBA;
3748 tf->lbah = (block >> 16) & 0xff;
3749 tf->lbam = (block >> 8) & 0xff;
3750 tf->lbal = block & 0xff;
3751 tf->hob_lbah = (block >> 40) & 0xff;
3752 tf->hob_lbam = (block >> 32) & 0xff;
3753 tf->hob_lbal = (block >> 24) & 0xff;
3754
3755 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_ISADDR | ATA_TFLAG_DEVICE | ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3756 qc->flags |= ATA_QCFLAG_RESULT_TF;
3757
3758 ata_qc_set_pc_nbytes(qc);
3759
3760 qc->complete_fn = ata_scsi_report_zones_complete;
3761
3762 return 0;
3763
3764invalid_fld:
3765 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(qc->dev, scmd, fp, bp);
3766 return 1;
3767
3768invalid_param_len:
3769 /* "Parameter list length error" */
3770 ata_scsi_set_sense(qc->dev, scmd, ILLEGAL_REQUEST, 0x1a, 0x0);
3771 return 1;
3772}
3773
3774static unsigned int ata_scsi_zbc_out_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
3775{
3776 struct ata_taskfile *tf = &qc->tf;
3777 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
3778 struct ata_device *dev = qc->dev;
3779 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
3780 u8 all, sa;
3781 u64 block;
3782 u32 n_block;
3783 u16 fp = (u16)-1;
3784
3785 if (unlikely(scmd->cmd_len < 16)) {
3786 fp = 15;
3787 goto invalid_fld;
3788 }
3789
3790 sa = cdb[1] & 0x1f;
3791 if ((sa != ZO_CLOSE_ZONE) && (sa != ZO_FINISH_ZONE) &&
3792 (sa != ZO_OPEN_ZONE) && (sa != ZO_RESET_WRITE_POINTER)) {
3793 fp = 1;
3794 goto invalid_fld;
3795 }
3796
3797 scsi_16_lba_len(cdb, &block, &n_block);
3798 if (n_block) {
3799 /*
3800 * ZAC MANAGEMENT OUT doesn't define any length
3801 */
3802 goto invalid_param_len;
3803 }
3804
3805 all = cdb[14] & 0x1;
3806 if (all) {
3807 /*
3808 * Ignore the block address (zone ID) as defined by ZBC.
3809 */
3810 block = 0;
3811 } else if (block >= dev->n_sectors) {
3812 /*
3813 * Block must be a valid zone ID (a zone start LBA).
3814 */
3815 fp = 2;
3816 goto invalid_fld;
3817 }
3818
3819 if (ata_ncq_enabled(qc->dev) &&
3820 ata_fpdma_zac_mgmt_out_supported(qc->dev)) {
3821 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NCQ_NODATA;
3822 tf->command = ATA_CMD_NCQ_NON_DATA;
3823 tf->feature = ATA_SUBCMD_NCQ_NON_DATA_ZAC_MGMT_OUT;
3824 tf->nsect = qc->tag << 3;
3825 tf->auxiliary = sa | ((u16)all << 8);
3826 } else {
3827 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NODATA;
3828 tf->command = ATA_CMD_ZAC_MGMT_OUT;
3829 tf->feature = sa;
3830 tf->hob_feature = all;
3831 }
3832 tf->lbah = (block >> 16) & 0xff;
3833 tf->lbam = (block >> 8) & 0xff;
3834 tf->lbal = block & 0xff;
3835 tf->hob_lbah = (block >> 40) & 0xff;
3836 tf->hob_lbam = (block >> 32) & 0xff;
3837 tf->hob_lbal = (block >> 24) & 0xff;
3838 tf->device = ATA_LBA;
3839 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_ISADDR | ATA_TFLAG_DEVICE | ATA_TFLAG_LBA48;
3840
3841 return 0;
3842
3843 invalid_fld:
3844 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(qc->dev, scmd, fp, 0xff);
3845 return 1;
3846invalid_param_len:
3847 /* "Parameter list length error" */
3848 ata_scsi_set_sense(qc->dev, scmd, ILLEGAL_REQUEST, 0x1a, 0x0);
3849 return 1;
3850}
3851
3852/**
3853 * ata_mselect_caching - Simulate MODE SELECT for caching info page
3854 * @qc: Storage for translated ATA taskfile
3855 * @buf: input buffer
3856 * @len: number of valid bytes in the input buffer
3857 * @fp: out parameter for the failed field on error
3858 *
3859 * Prepare a taskfile to modify caching information for the device.
3860 *
3861 * LOCKING:
3862 * None.
3863 */
3864static int ata_mselect_caching(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc,
3865 const u8 *buf, int len, u16 *fp)
3866{
3867 struct ata_taskfile *tf = &qc->tf;
3868 struct ata_device *dev = qc->dev;
3869 u8 mpage[CACHE_MPAGE_LEN];
3870 u8 wce;
3871 int i;
3872
3873 /*
3874 * The first two bytes of def_cache_mpage are a header, so offsets
3875 * in mpage are off by 2 compared to buf. Same for len.
3876 */
3877
3878 if (len != CACHE_MPAGE_LEN - 2) {
3879 if (len < CACHE_MPAGE_LEN - 2)
3880 *fp = len;
3881 else
3882 *fp = CACHE_MPAGE_LEN - 2;
3883 return -EINVAL;
3884 }
3885
3886 wce = buf[0] & (1 << 2);
3887
3888 /*
3889 * Check that read-only bits are not modified.
3890 */
3891 ata_msense_caching(dev->id, mpage, false);
3892 for (i = 0; i < CACHE_MPAGE_LEN - 2; i++) {
3893 if (i == 0)
3894 continue;
3895 if (mpage[i + 2] != buf[i]) {
3896 *fp = i;
3897 return -EINVAL;
3898 }
3899 }
3900
3901 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_DEVICE | ATA_TFLAG_ISADDR;
3902 tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NODATA;
3903 tf->nsect = 0;
3904 tf->command = ATA_CMD_SET_FEATURES;
3905 tf->feature = wce ? SETFEATURES_WC_ON : SETFEATURES_WC_OFF;
3906 return 0;
3907}
3908
3909/**
3910 * ata_mselect_control - Simulate MODE SELECT for control page
3911 * @qc: Storage for translated ATA taskfile
3912 * @buf: input buffer
3913 * @len: number of valid bytes in the input buffer
3914 * @fp: out parameter for the failed field on error
3915 *
3916 * Prepare a taskfile to modify caching information for the device.
3917 *
3918 * LOCKING:
3919 * None.
3920 */
3921static int ata_mselect_control(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc,
3922 const u8 *buf, int len, u16 *fp)
3923{
3924 struct ata_device *dev = qc->dev;
3925 u8 mpage[CONTROL_MPAGE_LEN];
3926 u8 d_sense;
3927 int i;
3928
3929 /*
3930 * The first two bytes of def_control_mpage are a header, so offsets
3931 * in mpage are off by 2 compared to buf. Same for len.
3932 */
3933
3934 if (len != CONTROL_MPAGE_LEN - 2) {
3935 if (len < CONTROL_MPAGE_LEN - 2)
3936 *fp = len;
3937 else
3938 *fp = CONTROL_MPAGE_LEN - 2;
3939 return -EINVAL;
3940 }
3941
3942 d_sense = buf[0] & (1 << 2);
3943
3944 /*
3945 * Check that read-only bits are not modified.
3946 */
3947 ata_msense_control(dev, mpage, false);
3948 for (i = 0; i < CONTROL_MPAGE_LEN - 2; i++) {
3949 if (i == 0)
3950 continue;
3951 if (mpage[2 + i] != buf[i]) {
3952 *fp = i;
3953 return -EINVAL;
3954 }
3955 }
3956 if (d_sense & (1 << 2))
3957 dev->flags |= ATA_DFLAG_D_SENSE;
3958 else
3959 dev->flags &= ~ATA_DFLAG_D_SENSE;
3960 return 0;
3961}

3963/**
3964 * ata_scsi_mode_select_xlat - Simulate MODE SELECT 6, 10 commands
3965 * @qc: Storage for translated ATA taskfile
3966 *
3967 * Converts a MODE SELECT command to an ATA SET FEATURES taskfile.
3968 * Assume this is invoked for direct access devices (e.g. disks) only.
3969 * There should be no block descriptor for other device types.
3970 *
3971 * LOCKING:
3972 * spin_lock_irqsave(host lock)
3973 */
3974static unsigned int ata_scsi_mode_select_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
3975{
3976 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
3977 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
3978 const u8 *p;
3979 u8 pg, spg;
3980 unsigned six_byte, pg_len, hdr_len, bd_len;
3981 int len;
3982 u16 fp = (u16)-1;
3983 u8 bp = 0xff;
3984
3985 VPRINTK("ENTER\n");
3986
3987 six_byte = (cdb[0] == MODE_SELECT);
3988 if (six_byte) {
3989 if (scmd->cmd_len < 5) {
3990 fp = 4;
3991 goto invalid_fld;
3992 }
3993
3994 len = cdb[4];
3995 hdr_len = 4;
3996 } else {
3997 if (scmd->cmd_len < 9) {
3998 fp = 8;
3999 goto invalid_fld;
4000 }
4001
4002 len = (cdb[7] << 8) + cdb[8];
4003 hdr_len = 8;
4004 }
4005
4006 /* We only support PF=1, SP=0. */
4007 if ((cdb[1] & 0x11) != 0x10) {
4008 fp = 1;
4009 bp = (cdb[1] & 0x01) ? 1 : 5;
4010 goto invalid_fld;
4011 }
4012
4013 /* Test early for possible overrun. */
4014 if (!scsi_sg_count(scmd) || scsi_sglist(scmd)->length < len)
4015 goto invalid_param_len;
4016
4017 p = page_address(sg_page(scsi_sglist(scmd)));
4018
4019 /* Move past header and block descriptors. */
4020 if (len < hdr_len)
4021 goto invalid_param_len;
4022
4023 if (six_byte)
4024 bd_len = p[3];
4025 else
4026 bd_len = (p[6] << 8) + p[7];
4027
4028 len -= hdr_len;
4029 p += hdr_len;
4030 if (len < bd_len)
4031 goto invalid_param_len;
4032 if (bd_len != 0 && bd_len != 8) {
4033 fp = (six_byte) ? 3 : 6;
4034 fp += bd_len + hdr_len;
4035 goto invalid_param;
4036 }
4037
4038 len -= bd_len;
4039 p += bd_len;
4040 if (len == 0)
4041 goto skip;
4042
4043 /* Parse both possible formats for the mode page headers. */
4044 pg = p[0] & 0x3f;
4045 if (p[0] & 0x40) {
4046 if (len < 4)
4047 goto invalid_param_len;
4048
4049 spg = p[1];
4050 pg_len = (p[2] << 8) | p[3];
4051 p += 4;
4052 len -= 4;
4053 } else {
4054 if (len < 2)
4055 goto invalid_param_len;
4056
4057 spg = 0;
4058 pg_len = p[1];
4059 p += 2;
4060 len -= 2;
4061 }
4062
4063 /*
4064 * No mode subpages supported (yet) but asking for _all_
4065 * subpages may be valid
4066 */
4067 if (spg && (spg != ALL_SUB_MPAGES)) {
4068 fp = (p[0] & 0x40) ? 1 : 0;
4069 fp += hdr_len + bd_len;
4070 goto invalid_param;
4071 }
4072 if (pg_len > len)
4073 goto invalid_param_len;
4074
4075 switch (pg) {
4076 case CACHE_MPAGE:
4077 if (ata_mselect_caching(qc, p, pg_len, &fp) < 0) {
4078 fp += hdr_len + bd_len;
4079 goto invalid_param;
4080 }
4081 break;
4082 case CONTROL_MPAGE:
4083 if (ata_mselect_control(qc, p, pg_len, &fp) < 0) {
4084 fp += hdr_len + bd_len;
4085 goto invalid_param;
4086 } else {
4087 goto skip; /* No ATA command to send */
4088 }
4089 break;
4090 default: /* invalid page code */
4091 fp = bd_len + hdr_len;
4092 goto invalid_param;
4093 }
4094
4095 /*
4096 * Only one page has changeable data, so we only support setting one
4097 * page at a time.
4098 */
4099 if (len > pg_len)
4100 goto invalid_param;
4101
4102 return 0;
4103
4104 invalid_fld:
4105 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(qc->dev, scmd, fp, bp);
4106 return 1;
4107
4108 invalid_param:
4109 ata_scsi_set_invalid_parameter(qc->dev, scmd, fp);
4110 return 1;
4111
4112 invalid_param_len:
4113 /* "Parameter list length error" */
4114 ata_scsi_set_sense(qc->dev, scmd, ILLEGAL_REQUEST, 0x1a, 0x0);
4115 return 1;
4116
4117 skip:
4118 scmd->result = SAM_STAT_GOOD;
4119 return 1;
4120}
4121
4122static u8 ata_scsi_trusted_op(u32 len, bool send, bool dma)
4123{
4124 if (len == 0)
4125 return ATA_CMD_TRUSTED_NONDATA;
4126 else if (send)
4127 return dma ? ATA_CMD_TRUSTED_SND_DMA : ATA_CMD_TRUSTED_SND;
4128 else
4129 return dma ? ATA_CMD_TRUSTED_RCV_DMA : ATA_CMD_TRUSTED_RCV;
4130}
4131
4132static unsigned int ata_scsi_security_inout_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
4133{
4134 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
4135 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
4136 struct ata_taskfile *tf = &qc->tf;
4137 u8 secp = cdb[1];
4138 bool send = (cdb[0] == SECURITY_PROTOCOL_OUT);
4139 u16 spsp = get_unaligned_be16(&cdb[2]);
4140 u32 len = get_unaligned_be32(&cdb[6]);
4141 bool dma = !(qc->dev->flags & ATA_DFLAG_PIO);
4142
4143 /*
4144 * We don't support the ATA "security" protocol.
4145 */
4146 if (secp == 0xef) {
4147 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(qc->dev, scmd, 1, 0);
4148 return 1;
4149 }
4150
4151 if (cdb[4] & 7) { /* INC_512 */
4152 if (len > 0xffff) {
4153 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(qc->dev, scmd, 6, 0);
4154 return 1;
4155 }
4156 } else {
4157 if (len > 0x01fffe00) {
4158 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(qc->dev, scmd, 6, 0);
4159 return 1;
4160 }
4161
4162 /* convert to the sector-based ATA addressing */
4163 len = (len + 511) / 512;
4164 }
4165
4166 tf->protocol = dma ? ATA_PROT_DMA : ATA_PROT_PIO;
4167 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_DEVICE | ATA_TFLAG_ISADDR | ATA_TFLAG_LBA;
4168 if (send)
4169 tf->flags |= ATA_TFLAG_WRITE;
4170 tf->command = ata_scsi_trusted_op(len, send, dma);
4171 tf->feature = secp;
4172 tf->lbam = spsp & 0xff;
4173 tf->lbah = spsp >> 8;
4174
4175 if (len) {
4176 tf->nsect = len & 0xff;
4177 tf->lbal = len >> 8;
4178 } else {
4179 if (!send)
4180 tf->lbah = (1 << 7);
4181 }
4182
4183 ata_qc_set_pc_nbytes(qc);
4184 return 0;
4185}

4187/**
4188 * ata_scsi_var_len_cdb_xlat - SATL variable length CDB to Handler
4189 * @qc: Command to be translated
4190 *
4191 * Translate a SCSI variable length CDB to specified commands.
4192 * It checks a service action value in CDB to call corresponding handler.
4193 *
4194 * RETURNS:
4195 * Zero on success, non-zero on failure
4196 *
4197 */
4198static unsigned int ata_scsi_var_len_cdb_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
4199{
4200 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd = qc->scsicmd;
4201 const u8 *cdb = scmd->cmnd;
4202 const u16 sa = get_unaligned_be16(&cdb[8]);
4203
4204 /*
4205 * if service action represents a ata pass-thru(32) command,
4206 * then pass it to ata_scsi_pass_thru handler.
4207 */
4208 if (sa == ATA_32)
4209 return ata_scsi_pass_thru(qc);
4210
4211 /* unsupported service action */
4212 return 1;
4213}

4215/**
4216 * ata_get_xlat_func - check if SCSI to ATA translation is possible
4217 * @dev: ATA device
4218 * @cmd: SCSI command opcode to consider
4219 *
4220 * Look up the SCSI command given, and determine whether the
4221 * SCSI command is to be translated or simulated.
4222 *
4223 * RETURNS:
4224 * Pointer to translation function if possible, %NULL if not.
4225 */
4226
4227static inline ata_xlat_func_t ata_get_xlat_func(struct ata_device *dev, u8 cmd)
4228{
4229 switch (cmd) {
4230 case READ_6:
4231 case READ_10:
4232 case READ_16:
4233
4234 case WRITE_6:
4235 case WRITE_10:
4236 case WRITE_16:
4237 return ata_scsi_rw_xlat;
4238
4239 case WRITE_SAME_16:
4240 return ata_scsi_write_same_xlat;
4241
4242 case SYNCHRONIZE_CACHE:
4243 if (ata_try_flush_cache(dev))
4244 return ata_scsi_flush_xlat;
4245 break;
4246
4247 case VERIFY:
4248 case VERIFY_16:
4249 return ata_scsi_verify_xlat;
4250
4251 case ATA_12:
4252 case ATA_16:
4253 return ata_scsi_pass_thru;
4254
4255 case VARIABLE_LENGTH_CMD:
4256 return ata_scsi_var_len_cdb_xlat;
4257
4258 case MODE_SELECT:
4259 case MODE_SELECT_10:
4260 return ata_scsi_mode_select_xlat;
4261 break;
4262
4263 case ZBC_IN:
4264 return ata_scsi_zbc_in_xlat;
4265
4266 case ZBC_OUT:
4267 return ata_scsi_zbc_out_xlat;
4268
4269 case SECURITY_PROTOCOL_IN:
4270 case SECURITY_PROTOCOL_OUT:
4271 if (!(dev->flags & ATA_DFLAG_TRUSTED))
4272 break;
4273 return ata_scsi_security_inout_xlat;
4274
4275 case START_STOP:
4276 return ata_scsi_start_stop_xlat;
4277 }
4278
4279 return NULL;
4280}

4282/**
4283 * ata_scsi_dump_cdb - dump SCSI command contents to dmesg
4284 * @ap: ATA port to which the command was being sent
4285 * @cmd: SCSI command to dump
4286 *
4287 * Prints the contents of a SCSI command via printk().
4288 */
4289
4290static inline void ata_scsi_dump_cdb(struct ata_port *ap,
4291 struct scsi_cmnd *cmd)
4292{
4293#ifdef ATA_DEBUG
4294 struct scsi_device *scsidev = cmd->device;
4295
4296 DPRINTK("CDB (%u:%d,%d,%lld) %9ph\n",

4302
4303static inline int __ata_scsi_queuecmd(struct scsi_cmnd *scmd,
4304 struct ata_device *dev)
4305{
4306 u8 scsi_op = scmd->cmnd[0];
4307 ata_xlat_func_t xlat_func;
4308 int rc = 0;
4309
4310 if (dev->class == ATA_DEV_ATA || dev->class == ATA_DEV_ZAC) {
4311 if (unlikely(!scmd->cmd_len || scmd->cmd_len > dev->cdb_len))
4312 goto bad_cdb_len;
4313
4314 xlat_func = ata_get_xlat_func(dev, scsi_op);
4315 } else {
4316 if (unlikely(!scmd->cmd_len))
4317 goto bad_cdb_len;
4318
4319 xlat_func = NULL;
4320 if (likely((scsi_op != ATA_16) || !atapi_passthru16)) {
4321 /* relay SCSI command to ATAPI device */
4322 int len = COMMAND_SIZE(scsi_op);
4323 if (unlikely(len > scmd->cmd_len ||
4324 len > dev->cdb_len ||
4325 scmd->cmd_len > ATAPI_CDB_LEN))
4326 goto bad_cdb_len;
4327
4328 xlat_func = atapi_xlat;
4329 } else {
4330 /* ATA_16 passthru, treat as an ATA command */
4331 if (unlikely(scmd->cmd_len > 16))
4332 goto bad_cdb_len;
4333
4334 xlat_func = ata_get_xlat_func(dev, scsi_op);
4335 }
4336 }
4337
4338 if (xlat_func)
4339 rc = ata_scsi_translate(dev, scmd, xlat_func);
4340 else
4341 ata_scsi_simulate(dev, scmd);
4342
4343 return rc;
4344
4345 bad_cdb_len:
4346 DPRINTK("bad CDB len=%u, scsi_op=0x%02x, max=%u\n",
4347 scmd->cmd_len, scsi_op, dev->cdb_len);
4348 scmd->result = DID_ERROR << 16;
4349 scmd->scsi_done(scmd);
4350 return 0;
4351}
4352
4353/**
4354 * ata_scsi_queuecmd - Issue SCSI cdb to libata-managed device
4355 * @shost: SCSI host of command to be sent
4356 * @cmd: SCSI command to be sent
4357 *
4358 * In some cases, this function translates SCSI commands into
4359 * ATA taskfiles, and queues the taskfiles to be sent to
4360 * hardware. In other cases, this function simulates a
4361 * SCSI device by evaluating and responding to certain
4362 * SCSI commands. This creates the overall effect of
4363 * ATA and ATAPI devices appearing as SCSI devices.
4364 *
4365 * LOCKING:
4366 * ATA host lock
4367 *
4368 * RETURNS:
4369 * Return value from __ata_scsi_queuecmd() if @cmd can be queued,
4370 * 0 otherwise.
4371 */
4372int ata_scsi_queuecmd(struct Scsi_Host *shost, struct scsi_cmnd *cmd)
4373{
4374 struct ata_port *ap;
4375 struct ata_device *dev;
4376 struct scsi_device *scsidev = cmd->device;
4377 int rc = 0;
4378 unsigned long irq_flags;
4379
4380 ap = ata_shost_to_port(shost);
4381
4382 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, irq_flags);
4383
4384 ata_scsi_dump_cdb(ap, cmd);
4385
4386 dev = ata_scsi_find_dev(ap, scsidev);
4387 if (likely(dev))
4388 rc = __ata_scsi_queuecmd(cmd, dev);
4389 else {
4390 cmd->result = (DID_BAD_TARGET << 16);
4391 cmd->scsi_done(cmd);
4392 }
4393
4394 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, irq_flags);
4395
4396 return rc;
4397}
4398
4399/**
4400 * ata_scsi_simulate - simulate SCSI command on ATA device
4401 * @dev: the target device
4402 * @cmd: SCSI command being sent to device.
4403 *
4404 * Interprets and directly executes a select list of SCSI commands
4405 * that can be handled internally.
4406 *
4407 * LOCKING:
4408 * spin_lock_irqsave(host lock)
4409 */
4410
4411void ata_scsi_simulate(struct ata_device *dev, struct scsi_cmnd *cmd)
4412{
4413 struct ata_scsi_args args;
4414 const u8 *scsicmd = cmd->cmnd;
4415 u8 tmp8;
4416
4417 args.dev = dev;
4418 args.id = dev->id;
4419 args.cmd = cmd;
4420
4421 switch(scsicmd[0]) {
4422 case INQUIRY:
4423 if (scsicmd[1] & 2) /* is CmdDt set? */
4424 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, cmd, 1, 0xff);
4425 else if ((scsicmd[1] & 1) == 0) /* is EVPD clear? */
4426 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_std);
4427 else switch (scsicmd[2]) {
4428 case 0x00:
4429 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_00);
4430 break;
4431 case 0x80:
4432 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_80);
4433 break;
4434 case 0x83:
4435 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_83);
4436 break;
4437 case 0x89:
4438 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_89);
4439 break;
4440 case 0xb0:
4441 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_b0);
4442 break;
4443 case 0xb1:
4444 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_b1);
4445 break;
4446 case 0xb2:
4447 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_b2);
4448 break;
4449 case 0xb6:
4450 if (dev->flags & ATA_DFLAG_ZAC) {
4451 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_inq_b6);
4452 break;
4453 }
4454 /* Fallthrough */
4455 default:
4456 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, cmd, 2, 0xff);
4457 break;
4458 }
4459 break;
4460
4461 case MODE_SENSE:
4462 case MODE_SENSE_10:
4463 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_mode_sense);
4464 break;
4465
4466 case READ_CAPACITY:
4467 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_read_cap);
4468 break;
4469
4470 case SERVICE_ACTION_IN_16:
4471 if ((scsicmd[1] & 0x1f) == SAI_READ_CAPACITY_16)
4472 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_read_cap);
4473 else
4474 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, cmd, 1, 0xff);
4475 break;
4476
4477 case REPORT_LUNS:
4478 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_report_luns);
4479 break;
4480
4481 case REQUEST_SENSE:
4482 ata_scsi_set_sense(dev, cmd, 0, 0, 0);
4483 cmd->result = (DRIVER_SENSE << 24);
4484 break;
4485
4486 /* if we reach this, then writeback caching is disabled,
4487 * turning this into a no-op.
4488 */
4489 case SYNCHRONIZE_CACHE:
4490 /* fall through */
4491
4492 /* no-op's, complete with success */
4493 case REZERO_UNIT:
4494 case SEEK_6:
4495 case SEEK_10:
4496 case TEST_UNIT_READY:
4497 break;
4498
4499 case SEND_DIAGNOSTIC:
4500 tmp8 = scsicmd[1] & ~(1 << 3);
4501 if (tmp8 != 0x4 || scsicmd[3] || scsicmd[4])
4502 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, cmd, 1, 0xff);
4503 break;
4504
4505 case MAINTENANCE_IN:
4506 if (scsicmd[1] == MI_REPORT_SUPPORTED_OPERATION_CODES)
4507 ata_scsi_rbuf_fill(&args, ata_scsiop_maint_in);
4508 else
4509 ata_scsi_set_invalid_field(dev, cmd, 1, 0xff);
4510 break;
4511
4512 /* all other commands */
4513 default:
4514 ata_scsi_set_sense(dev, cmd, ILLEGAL_REQUEST, 0x20, 0x0);
4515 /* "Invalid command operation code" */
4516 break;
4517 }
4518
4519 cmd->scsi_done(cmd);
4520}
4521
4522int ata_scsi_add_hosts(struct ata_host *host, struct scsi_host_template *sht)
4523{
4524 int i, rc;
4525
4526 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++) {
4527 struct ata_port *ap = host->ports[i];
4528 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
4529
4530 rc = -ENOMEM;
4531 shost = scsi_host_alloc(sht, sizeof(struct ata_port *));
4532 if (!shost)
4533 goto err_alloc;
4534
4535 shost->eh_noresume = 1;
4536 *(struct ata_port **)&shost->hostdata[0] = ap;
4537 ap->scsi_host = shost;
4538
4539 shost->transportt = ata_scsi_transport_template;
4540 shost->unique_id = ap->print_id;
4541 shost->max_id = 16;
4542 shost->max_lun = 1;
4543 shost->max_channel = 1;
4544 shost->max_cmd_len = 32;
4545
4546 /* Schedule policy is determined by ->qc_defer()
4547 * callback and it needs to see every deferred qc.
4548 * Set host_blocked to 1 to prevent SCSI midlayer from
4549 * automatically deferring requests.
4550 */
4551 shost->max_host_blocked = 1;
4552
4553 rc = scsi_add_host_with_dma(ap->scsi_host,
4554 &ap->tdev, ap->host->dev);
4555 if (rc)
4556 goto err_add;
4557 }
4558
4559 return 0;
4560
4561 err_add:
4562 scsi_host_put(host->ports[i]->scsi_host);
4563 err_alloc:
4564 while (--i >= 0) {
4565 struct Scsi_Host *shost = host->ports[i]->scsi_host;
4566
4567 scsi_remove_host(shost);
4568 scsi_host_put(shost);
4569 }
4570 return rc;
4571}
4572
4573void ata_scsi_scan_host(struct ata_port *ap, int sync)
4574{
4575 int tries = 5;
4576 struct ata_device *last_failed_dev = NULL;
4577 struct ata_link *link;
4578 struct ata_device *dev;
4579
4580 repeat:
4581 ata_for_each_link(link, ap, EDGE) {
4582 ata_for_each_dev(dev, link, ENABLED) {
4583 struct scsi_device *sdev;
4584 int channel = 0, id = 0;
4585
4586 if (dev->sdev)
4587 continue;
4588
4589 if (ata_is_host_link(link))
4590 id = dev->devno;
4591 else
4592 channel = link->pmp;
4593
4594 sdev = __scsi_add_device(ap->scsi_host, channel, id, 0,
4595 NULL);
4596 if (!IS_ERR(sdev)) {
4597 dev->sdev = sdev;
4598 scsi_device_put(sdev);
4599 } else {
4600 dev->sdev = NULL;
4601 }
4602 }
4603 }
4604
4605 /* If we scanned while EH was in progress or allocation
4606 * failure occurred, scan would have failed silently. Check
4607 * whether all devices are attached.
4608 */
4609 ata_for_each_link(link, ap, EDGE) {
4610 ata_for_each_dev(dev, link, ENABLED) {
4611 if (!dev->sdev)
4612 goto exit_loop;
4613 }
4614 }
4615 exit_loop:
4616 if (!link)
4617 return;
4618
4619 /* we're missing some SCSI devices */
4620 if (sync) {
4621 /* If caller requested synchrnous scan && we've made
4622 * any progress, sleep briefly and repeat.
4623 */
4624 if (dev != last_failed_dev) {
4625 msleep(100);
4626 last_failed_dev = dev;
4627 goto repeat;
4628 }
4629
4630 /* We might be failing to detect boot device, give it
4631 * a few more chances.
4632 */
4633 if (--tries) {
4634 msleep(100);
4635 goto repeat;
4636 }
4637
4638 ata_port_err(ap,
4639 "WARNING: synchronous SCSI scan failed without making any progress, switching to async\n");
4640 }
4641
4642 queue_delayed_work(system_long_wq, &ap->hotplug_task,
4643 round_jiffies_relative(HZ));
4644}

4646/**
4647 * ata_scsi_offline_dev - offline attached SCSI device
4648 * @dev: ATA device to offline attached SCSI device for
4649 *
4650 * This function is called from ata_eh_hotplug() and responsible
4651 * for taking the SCSI device attached to @dev offline. This
4652 * function is called with host lock which protects dev->sdev
4653 * against clearing.
4654 *
4655 * LOCKING:
4656 * spin_lock_irqsave(host lock)
4657 *
4658 * RETURNS:
4659 * 1 if attached SCSI device exists, 0 otherwise.
4660 */
4661int ata_scsi_offline_dev(struct ata_device *dev)
4662{
4663 if (dev->sdev) {
4664 scsi_device_set_state(dev->sdev, SDEV_OFFLINE);
4665 return 1;
4666 }
4667 return 0;
4668}

4670/**
4671 * ata_scsi_remove_dev - remove attached SCSI device
4672 * @dev: ATA device to remove attached SCSI device for
4673 *
4674 * This function is called from ata_eh_scsi_hotplug() and
4675 * responsible for removing the SCSI device attached to @dev.
4676 *
4677 * LOCKING:
4678 * Kernel thread context (may sleep).
4679 */
4680static void ata_scsi_remove_dev(struct ata_device *dev)
4681{
4682 struct ata_port *ap = dev->link->ap;
4683 struct scsi_device *sdev;
4684 unsigned long flags;
4685
4686 /* Alas, we need to grab scan_mutex to ensure SCSI device
4687 * state doesn't change underneath us and thus
4688 * scsi_device_get() always succeeds. The mutex locking can
4689 * be removed if there is __scsi_device_get() interface which
4690 * increments reference counts regardless of device state.
4691 */
4692 mutex_lock(&ap->scsi_host->scan_mutex);
4693 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, flags);
4694
4695 /* clearing dev->sdev is protected by host lock */
4696 sdev = dev->sdev;
4697 dev->sdev = NULL;
4698
4699 if (sdev) {
4700 /* If user initiated unplug races with us, sdev can go
4701 * away underneath us after the host lock and
4702 * scan_mutex are released. Hold onto it.
4703 */
4704 if (scsi_device_get(sdev) == 0) {
4705 /* The following ensures the attached sdev is
4706 * offline on return from ata_scsi_offline_dev()
4707 * regardless it wins or loses the race
4708 * against this function.
4709 */
4710 scsi_device_set_state(sdev, SDEV_OFFLINE);
4711 } else {
4712 WARN_ON(1);
4713 sdev = NULL;
4714 }
4715 }
4716
4717 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
4718 mutex_unlock(&ap->scsi_host->scan_mutex);
4719
4720 if (sdev) {
4721 ata_dev_info(dev, "detaching (SCSI %s)\n",
4722 dev_name(&sdev->sdev_gendev));
4723
4724 scsi_remove_device(sdev);
4725 scsi_device_put(sdev);
4726 }
4727}
4728
4729static void ata_scsi_handle_link_detach(struct ata_link *link)
4730{
4731 struct ata_port *ap = link->ap;
4732 struct ata_device *dev;
4733
4734 ata_for_each_dev(dev, link, ALL) {
4735 unsigned long flags;
4736
4737 if (!(dev->flags & ATA_DFLAG_DETACHED))
4738 continue;
4739
4740 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, flags);
4741 dev->flags &= ~ATA_DFLAG_DETACHED;
4742 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
4743
4744 if (zpodd_dev_enabled(dev))
4745 zpodd_exit(dev);
4746
4747 ata_scsi_remove_dev(dev);
4748 }
4749}

4768/**
4769 * ata_scsi_hotplug - SCSI part of hotplug
4770 * @work: Pointer to ATA port to perform SCSI hotplug on
4771 *
4772 * Perform SCSI part of hotplug. It's executed from a separate
4773 * workqueue after EH completes. This is necessary because SCSI
4774 * hot plugging requires working EH and hot unplugging is
4775 * synchronized with hot plugging with a mutex.
4776 *
4777 * LOCKING:
4778 * Kernel thread context (may sleep).
4779 */
4780void ata_scsi_hotplug(struct work_struct *work)
4781{
4782 struct ata_port *ap =
4783 container_of(work, struct ata_port, hotplug_task.work);
4784 int i;
4785
4786 if (ap->pflags & ATA_PFLAG_UNLOADING) {
4787 DPRINTK("ENTER/EXIT - unloading\n");
4788 return;
4789 }
4790
4791 /*
4792 * XXX - UGLY HACK
4793 *
4794 * The block layer suspend/resume path is fundamentally broken due
4795 * to freezable kthreads and workqueue and may deadlock if a block
4796 * device gets removed while resume is in progress. I don't know
4797 * what the solution is short of removing freezable kthreads and
4798 * workqueues altogether.
4799 *
4800 * The following is an ugly hack to avoid kicking off device
4801 * removal while freezer is active. This is a joke but does avoid
4802 * this particular deadlock scenario.
4803 *
4804 * https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=62801
4805 * http://marc.info/?l=linux-kernel&m=138695698516487
4806 */
4807#ifdef CONFIG_FREEZER
4808 while (pm_freezing)
4809 msleep(10);
4810#endif
4811
4812 DPRINTK("ENTER\n");
4813 mutex_lock(&ap->scsi_scan_mutex);
4814
4815 /* Unplug detached devices. We cannot use link iterator here
4816 * because PMP links have to be scanned even if PMP is
4817 * currently not attached. Iterate manually.
4818 */
4819 ata_scsi_handle_link_detach(&ap->link);
4820 if (ap->pmp_link)
4821 for (i = 0; i < SATA_PMP_MAX_PORTS; i++)
4822 ata_scsi_handle_link_detach(&ap->pmp_link[i]);
4823
4824 /* scan for new ones */
4825 ata_scsi_scan_host(ap, 0);
4826
4827 mutex_unlock(&ap->scsi_scan_mutex);
4828 DPRINTK("EXIT\n");
4829}

4831/**
4832 * ata_scsi_user_scan - indication for user-initiated bus scan
4833 * @shost: SCSI host to scan
4834 * @channel: Channel to scan
4835 * @id: ID to scan
4836 * @lun: LUN to scan
4837 *
4838 * This function is called when user explicitly requests bus
4839 * scan. Set probe pending flag and invoke EH.
4840 *
4841 * LOCKING:
4842 * SCSI layer (we don't care)
4843 *
4844 * RETURNS:
4845 * Zero.
4846 */
4847int ata_scsi_user_scan(struct Scsi_Host *shost, unsigned int channel,
4848 unsigned int id, u64 lun)
4849{
4850 struct ata_port *ap = ata_shost_to_port(shost);
4851 unsigned long flags;
4852 int devno, rc = 0;
4853
4854 if (!ap->ops->error_handler)
4855 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
4856
4857 if (lun != SCAN_WILD_CARD && lun)
4858 return -EINVAL;
4859
4860 if (!sata_pmp_attached(ap)) {
4861 if (channel != SCAN_WILD_CARD && channel)
4862 return -EINVAL;
4863 devno = id;
4864 } else {
4865 if (id != SCAN_WILD_CARD && id)
4866 return -EINVAL;
4867 devno = channel;
4868 }
4869
4870 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, flags);
4871
4872 if (devno == SCAN_WILD_CARD) {
4873 struct ata_link *link;
4874
4875 ata_for_each_link(link, ap, EDGE) {
4876 struct ata_eh_info *ehi = &link->eh_info;
4877 ehi->probe_mask |= ATA_ALL_DEVICES;
4878 ehi->action |= ATA_EH_RESET;
4879 }
4880 } else {
4881 struct ata_device *dev = ata_find_dev(ap, devno);
4882
4883 if (dev) {
4884 struct ata_eh_info *ehi = &dev->link->eh_info;
4885 ehi->probe_mask |= 1 << dev->devno;
4886 ehi->action |= ATA_EH_RESET;
4887 } else
4888 rc = -EINVAL;
4889 }
4890
4891 if (rc == 0) {
4892 ata_port_schedule_eh(ap);
4893 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
4894 ata_port_wait_eh(ap);
4895 } else
4896 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
4897
4898 return rc;
4899}

4901/**
4902 * ata_scsi_dev_rescan - initiate scsi_rescan_device()
4903 * @work: Pointer to ATA port to perform scsi_rescan_device()
4904 *
4905 * After ATA pass thru (SAT) commands are executed successfully,
4906 * libata need to propagate the changes to SCSI layer.
4907 *
4908 * LOCKING:
4909 * Kernel thread context (may sleep).
4910 */
4911void ata_scsi_dev_rescan(struct work_struct *work)
4912{
4913 struct ata_port *ap =
4914 container_of(work, struct ata_port, scsi_rescan_task);
4915 struct ata_link *link;
4916 struct ata_device *dev;
4917 unsigned long flags;
4918
4919 mutex_lock(&ap->scsi_scan_mutex);
4920 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, flags);
4921
4922 ata_for_each_link(link, ap, EDGE) {
4923 ata_for_each_dev(dev, link, ENABLED) {
4924 struct scsi_device *sdev = dev->sdev;
4925
4926 if (!sdev)
4927 continue;
4928 if (scsi_device_get(sdev))
4929 continue;
4930
4931 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
4932 scsi_rescan_device(&(sdev->sdev_gendev));
4933 scsi_device_put(sdev);
4934 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, flags);
4935 }
4936 }
4937
4938 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
4939 mutex_unlock(&ap->scsi_scan_mutex);
4940}

5090/**

5092 * @cmd: SCSI command to be sent
5093 * @ap: ATA port to which the command is being sent
5094 *
5095 * RETURNS:
5096 * Return value from __ata_scsi_queuecmd() if @cmd can be queued,

5100int ata_sas_queuecmd(struct scsi_cmnd *cmd, struct ata_port *ap)

5107 rc = __ata_scsi_queuecmd(cmd, ap->link.device);

5116int ata_sas_allocate_tag(struct ata_port *ap)
5117{
5118 unsigned int max_queue = ap->host->n_tags;
5119 unsigned int i, tag;
5120
5121 for (i = 0, tag = ap->sas_last_tag + 1; i < max_queue; i++, tag++) {
5122 tag = tag < max_queue ? tag : 0;
5123
5124 /* the last tag is reserved for internal command. */
5125 if (tag == ATA_TAG_INTERNAL)
5126 continue;
5127
5128 if (!test_and_set_bit(tag, &ap->sas_tag_allocated)) {
5129 ap->sas_last_tag = tag;
5130 return tag;
5131 }
5132 }
5133 return -1;
5134}

5136void ata_sas_free_tag(unsigned int tag, struct ata_port *ap)
5137{
5138 clear_bit(tag, &ap->sas_tag_allocated);
5139}
